I ordered from Uber Eats since I am unable to leave work at the moment. Anytime I order with a delivery service I set the bar pretty low. I know food is best fresh, within a few minutes. I ordered the Hades Bowl. The food was decent however, extremely salty. The to-go packaging could use more forethought. Paper instead of plastic. Paper bags will reduce the humidity and prevent food from arriving soggy. For orders being sent out by carrier, the bags should be sealed by staple to prevent tampering. Anything that should be crunchy such as the fried onion strings should be packed separately as to not allow them to get soggy on top of the rest of the food. These are merely suggestions and not a complaint. I will try the place again, in person but will not be ordering take out.

This was our third time ordering from here. The first two times we loved it, so I hate even giving it a 2 star rating. However, this time, we ordered through Grubhub. The food was cold, the drinks we ordered did not come, the wax paper On the inside of their foil wrapping stuck to the cheese of our kids pizza(we had to take all of the cheese of so there were not eating wax paper), and the added sauces requested on the side were not there. All of this would have been easily forgiven, but when we contacted grubhub with these issues, they place you on hold and contact the restaurant you ordered from. The Grubhub representative was told from Meraki that we would not be refunded or discounted. If there was any kind of apology or even future discount we would have chalked it up to a busy night and continued to eat there. The lack of caring about the issues with our order is not a good customer service. Grubhub showed more remorse and gave us 20% off of our next order. We sadly will not be eating here again.

Fiasco, start to finish.  Let’s start with the good things about the restaraunt:  - the food tasted good - the staff is friendly - they have an open dining experience that allows you to enjoy good weather while eating - they have a lot of options on their menu.  There were some major drawbacks though:  - the ordering system is confusing and the servers don’t help you through it. I walked inside and went to sit outside assuming I would have a menu brought to me and someone would ask me what I wanted to order. The server even said she would be right with me when I entered the restaurant. After being completely ignored for about 15 minutes despite how the restaurant only had a couple patrons I figured I misunderstood something. I went inside and realized my mistake. You order at the counter or get ignored. - after ordering they got every single item I ordered wrong. The meat was not what I had ordered and they didn’t bring me my beverage at all. - the servers don’t check on you while you eat. If there was a mistake in your order you aren’t given any ways to remedy it unless you want to wait in a long line. - The refund system is inefficient. Because I didn’t get my beverage I settled for a refund. It took at least 5 minutes start to finish, primarily because you’re forced to wait in a long line to ask for it. The line moves slowly because they take orders on a first come first served basis, regardless if the people in front of the line don’t know what they want yet.

This place is tremendous! Very helpful staff and amazing food. Unlike any Med Mix or other "traditional" Greek I've ever had, fantastic beer, too. Anytime I'm in Boise, I'm eating here. They just made a tradition in my own life!

We were wandering around today and wanted a bite to eat and found Meraki.  It was a great dining experience!  Immediately upon entering someone greeted us and explained the menu, showed us options and answered questions.  The portion sizes were perfect, the flavors were fabulous and the prices were reasonable.  And I was thoroughly excited about the soda options!!  If you are hanging out in downtown Boise, try out Meraki for some great Greek street food.
